### Protocol Type Definitions for MCP (Go)

Source: https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/go-sdk/blob/main/design/design.md

Defines core data structures used in the Model Context Protocol, generated from a JSON schema. These types, such as ReadResourceParams and CallToolResult, are essential for defining requests, responses, and data payloads within the protocol. It also illustrates the handling of union types using interfaces and structs.

```go
package mcp

import "encoding/json"

// ReadResourceParams defines the parameters for reading a resource.
type ReadResourceParams struct {
	URI string `json:"uri"`
}

// Meta includes arbitrary data and progress information.
type Meta struct {
	ArbitraryData map[string]any `json:"_meta,omitempty"`
	ProgressToken string       `json:"progress_token,omitempty"`
}

// CallToolResult represents the outcome of a tool call.
type CallToolResult struct {
	Meta    Meta      `json:"_meta,omitempty"`
	Content []Content `json:"content"`
	IsError bool      `json:"isError,omitempty"`
}

// Content is an interface representing different types of content (e.g., TextContent, ImageContent).
type Content interface {
	// (unexported methods)
}

// TextContent represents textual content.
type TextContent struct {
	Text string
}

// ImageContent represents image content.
type ImageContent struct {
	// Image specific fields
}

// AudioContent represents audio content.
type AudioContent struct {
	// Audio specific fields
}

// EmbeddedResource represents embedded resource content.
type EmbeddedResource struct {
	// Embedded resource specific fields
}

// ResourceContents is a struct with optional fields for different resource content types.
type ResourceContents struct {
	Text    *TextContent
	Image   *ImageContent
	Audio   *AudioContent
	Content *EmbeddedResource
}

```

